.TH man 8 "23 February 2025" "1.0" "banner-commenter man page"
.SH NAME
banner-commenter \- display input text into a banner

.SH SYNOPSIS
banner-commenter [OPTIONS...] [MESSAGE]

.SH DESCRIPTION
banner-commenter is a simple program that will display input text in a formatted banner, great for breaking up code into sections

.SH OPTIONS
Options are supplied with the "-" flag. There are several

.SH ALL OPTIONS

.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-show-config =\fISHOW_CONFIG\fR
Display the config values that the tool is using to calculate the margins/padding.

.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-padding =\fIPADDING\fR
Set the padding value.

.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-margin =\fIMARGIN\fR
Set the padding value.

.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-length =\fILENGTH\fR
Set the length value.

.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-out =\fIOUT\fR
Set the output path.

.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version =\fIVERSION\fR
Display the version.

.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help =\fIHELP\fR
Show help page.

.\".SH SEE ALSO
.\"cmd(8), cmd(5), cmd(8) 

.SH BUGS
No known bugs.

.SH AUTHOR
Christian Valenzuela (chris.a.valenzuela@protonmail.com)

